The collateral pledged to cover Lombard loans, OTC derivatives positions and securities lending and repo transactions consists primarily of readily marketable securities. Credit risk secured/not secured including mortgages

The Group’s internal guidelines accept more types of securities as loan collateral than are authorised by Swiss capital adequacy regulations under the standard approach. While this means that all loans are classified as overcollateralised according to

the Group’s internal concepts, it also means that, according to the standard approach, some loans are classified as either partially or entirely unsecured for regulatory purposes.
